<TITLE> First EU president must be from euro zone:France </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The first president of the European Union will have to be from a member state that has the euro as its currency as well as meeting other criteria, France's junior minister for European affairs said on Tuesday. Former British Prime Minister Tony Blair has made known his interest in the new post of president of the European Council, and his close ties to President Nicolas Sarkozy have led some observers to speculate that Paris would support him for the job. But French Secretary of State for European Affairs Jean-Pierre Jouyet seemed to rule that out when he listed three characteristics the future president must have. "The first quality is that they must have a rather strong leadership and charisma to be respected by their colleagues. That is at least the French vision -- it is not a vision that is shared by everybody," Jouyet told a group of economic reporters. "The second quality is that it is a person who obviously must be authentically European, understand the sensibility, its history, know the mechanisms and the institutional relations between the Council, the European Parliament ... and the Commission," Jouyet said. bdnews24.com/lq/1821hrs That would favour Luxembourg Prime Minister Jean-Claude Juncker, the centre-right chairman of finance ministers of the 15-nation euro zone, who has been at the heart of every European compromise since he came to power in 1995. Diplomats say Juncker is in a leading position for the post. "The third condition is that it must be a person who is at the heart of the solidarities that exist in Europe. These solidarities are the euro zone and the Schengen zone," Jouyet said, referring to the group of 24 states stretching from Estonia to Portugal within which border checks have been axed. Britain is not a member of Schengen or of the euro, although Blair spoke in favour of joining the single currency early in his 10-year premiership, which ended in June. Jouyet declined to identify particular can